{"questionId":"13911","questionHtml":"<p>Find the value of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"k\">\n  <mi>k</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"color:#999;font-size:90%;font-style:italic;\">* This question is from an exam for a previous syllabus, and may contain minor differences in marking or structure.</p><p>attempt to find <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"d\">\n  <mi>d</mi>\n</math></span> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>eg&nbsp; &nbsp;1.4&nbsp;− 1.3 ,&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{u_1} - {u_2}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>u</mi>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>u</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> ,&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"1.4 = 1.3 + \\left( {2 - 1} \\right)d\">\n  <mn>1.4</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1.3</mn>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mi>d</mi>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"d = 0.1\">\n  <mi>d</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0.1</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;(may be seen in expression for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{u_n}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>u</mi>\n      <mi>n</mi>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>correct equation&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>eg&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"1.3 + \\left( {k - 1} \\right) \\times 0.1 = 31.2\">\n  <mn>1.3</mn>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>k</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mn>0.1</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>31.2</mn>\n</math></span> ,&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"0.1k = 30\">\n  <mn>0.1</mn>\n  <mi>k</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>30</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"k = 300\">\n  <mi>k</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>300</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1&nbsp; N3</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:start;\"><em><strong><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Verdana' , sans-serif;color:black;\">[4 marks]</span></strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13911","referenceCode":"19M.2.SL.TZ2.S_10a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the value of k .","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.2—Arithmetic sequences and series"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}